subSubSection.paragraph:
h) 
Fruits and seeds
: The fruits are flat compressed, slightly elevated in the region of the seeds, elastically dehiscent and oblong. They have colors light green (
Fig. 6H
) with reddish spots, and reddish-brown (
Fig. 6G
) or ferruginous when mature, and are recovered by trichomes pubescent (
Fig. 6G
), hispid-setose (
Fig. 6F
) or puberulent (
Fig. 6H
). The seeds are oblong, orbicular or rhombic, with a smooth or slightly faveolated surface, possess colors light brown or dark and measure 
3–7 mm
long.
